Geometric meaning

There are really two stories here.

Story 1: polygon → circle

This measures how far a regular n-gon is from the circle under fixed area.

That ratio tends to 1 as n grows.

Story 2: circle → square

This measures the boundary distortion between the equal-area circle and equal-area square.

That ratio is universal and directly encodes \pi.

So the deeper statement is:

\pi appears as the invariant conversion constant between the circle’s optimal boundary and the square’s boundary under area preservation.

