Compact summary

For a regular n-gon of side length a, equal-area transforms give:

A_n=\frac{n a^2}{4\tan(\pi/n)}

P_n=na

C_n=a\sqrt{\frac{\pi n}{\tan(\pi/n)}}

P_{\square,n}=2a\sqrt{\frac{n}{\tan(\pi/n)}}

with ratios:

\boxed{R_{PC}(n)=\sqrt{\frac{\pi}{n\tan(\pi/n)}}}

\boxed{R_{CS}(n)=\frac{2}{\sqrt{\pi}}}

\boxed{R_{PS}(n)=2\sqrt{\frac{1}{n\tan(\pi/n)}}}

and as n\to\infty,

R_{PC}(n)\to 1

R_{PS}(n)\to \frac{2}{\sqrt{\pi}}

